1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,503
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,586 --> 00:00:08,258
["Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,341 --> 00:00:10,593
- <i>♪ Fix this</i> ♪
- <i>♪ Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,677 --> 00:00:12,804
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:12,887 --> 00:00:16,641
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

6
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:18,476
♪ <i>Knows too much</i> ♪

7
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:19,811
- <i>♪ Knows too much</i> ♪
- [crowd cheering]

8
00:00:19,894 --> 00:00:21,771
[Atoy] <i>You even took a nosedive</i>
<i>just to escape, huh?</i>

9
00:00:22,397 --> 00:00:23,606
[Atoy] Come on. Come with me!

10
00:00:23,690 --> 00:00:26,234
[Emerson] <i>Does that mean</i>
<i>he might have kidnapped Tonet too?</i>

11
00:00:26,317 --> 00:00:27,402
[Atoy] <i>Where does Enzo live?</i>

12
00:00:27,485 --> 00:00:29,404
[Raki] <i>They're the ones</i>
<i>close to him. Ask them.</i>

13
00:00:29,487 --> 00:00:32,532
Looks like the effect
of my special drink is potent.

14
00:00:32,615 --> 00:00:34,576
Enzo is holding Queenie.

15
00:00:34,659 --> 00:00:35,785
[Atoy] <i>He's the kidnapper.</i>

16
00:00:35,869 --> 00:00:37,203
Your replacement is already here.

17
00:00:37,954 --> 00:00:41,291
[Enzo] <i>She's in the living room, resting.</i>

18
00:00:41,875 --> 00:00:42,709
Tonet.

19
00:00:42,792 --> 00:00:43,918
PREVIOUSLY

20
00:00:44,002 --> 00:00:44,878
Tonet!

21
00:00:44,961 --> 00:00:47,881
[Atoy] <i>Is there a nearby farm here</i>
<i>or a goat pen?</i>

22
00:00:47,964 --> 00:00:48,798
[Raki] <i>There is.</i>

23
00:00:48,882 --> 00:00:50,592
[Emerson] <i>If something bad</i>
<i>happens to my sister,</i>

24
00:00:50,675 --> 00:00:53,011
<i>I'll never forgive myself.</i>

25
00:00:53,094 --> 00:00:56,389
[Atoy] I know you won't let anything
happen to her because she's your sister.

26
00:00:56,473 --> 00:00:58,141
I'll just check on my cat.

27
00:00:58,224 --> 00:01:01,352
Your replacement is here,
so don't make any noise!

28
00:01:01,436 --> 00:01:02,729
[grunting and groaning]

29
00:01:03,563 --> 00:01:04,773
[Enzo] <i>Tonet!</i>

30
00:01:05,356 --> 00:01:06,357
<i>Tonet, where are you?!</i>

31
00:01:06,441 --> 00:01:07,400
<i>Tonet!</i>

32
00:01:08,234 --> 00:01:09,486
<i>Tonet, where are you?!</i>

33
00:01:09,569 --> 00:01:10,820
[panting]

34
00:01:10,904 --> 00:01:12,072
[Enzo] <i>Where are you going, huh?</i>

35
00:01:12,155 --> 00:01:12,822
[grunts, groans]

36
00:01:12,906 --> 00:01:14,532
[Enzo] <i>No one escapes me!</i>

37
00:01:14,616 --> 00:01:17,285
[Atoy] <i>That Enzo, you don't know</i>
<i>what he might do to you.</i>

38
00:01:17,368 --> 00:01:18,953
<i>Stay here. That's the plan.</i>

39
00:01:19,037 --> 00:01:20,371
[Enzo] Who are you?

40
00:01:20,455 --> 00:01:21,998
What are you doing here?

41
00:01:22,082 --> 00:01:24,000
[music fades]

42
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:29,923
Uh, um… The battery died.

43
00:01:30,590 --> 00:01:32,050
Tow it.

44
00:01:32,133 --> 00:01:33,551
You can't park here.

45
00:01:33,635 --> 00:01:35,011
Huh?

46
00:01:35,094 --> 00:01:37,972
There! That's Enzo.

47
00:01:38,056 --> 00:01:40,058
[suspicious music playing]

48
00:01:40,141 --> 00:01:44,479
I've been calling,
but I can't contact anyone.

49
00:01:45,980 --> 00:01:48,733
Perhaps… Perhaps you have a car here.

50
00:01:48,817 --> 00:01:51,903
Maybe you can help me, bro,
just to jump-start my car.

51
00:01:51,986 --> 00:01:53,196
I don't have the key.

52
00:01:53,279 --> 00:01:54,280
- Please leave now.
- [Emerson] Huh?

53
00:01:55,698 --> 00:01:57,909
What about… maybe, water.

54
00:01:58,910 --> 00:02:00,787
- [stutters]
- [gun cocks]

55
00:02:00,870 --> 00:02:02,622
[ominous music playing]

56
00:02:02,705 --> 00:02:04,749
Who are you? Are you a cop?

57
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:06,960
Don't… don't… don't reveal yourself.

58
00:02:07,043 --> 00:02:08,795
Don't get caught. Don't die.

59
00:02:08,878 --> 00:02:10,588
Don't reveal yourself. Don't get caught--

60
00:02:10,672 --> 00:02:11,756
- Hey!
- [gasps]

61
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:13,007
Are you crazy?

62
00:02:14,259 --> 00:02:15,468
Come with me.

63
00:02:15,552 --> 00:02:16,636
- Huh?
- Come here.

64
00:02:16,719 --> 00:02:18,054
- Huh?
- Come with me.

65
00:02:18,138 --> 00:02:20,140
- What did you say-- Where?
- Come with me.

66
00:02:20,223 --> 00:02:22,392
- Where?
- [indistinct]

67
00:02:22,475 --> 00:02:24,978
No one said I'd go.

68
00:02:25,645 --> 00:02:27,522
- [Enzo] Come with me.
- [Emerson mutters]

69
00:02:27,605 --> 00:02:30,733
- [music fades]
- [crickets chirping]

70
00:02:32,735 --> 00:02:35,196
[suspicious music playing]

71
00:02:44,581 --> 00:02:47,292
I'm not a cop, not a special person.

72
00:02:48,042 --> 00:02:50,003
I just need to find my sister.

73
00:02:50,086 --> 00:02:51,129
Where did you hide Tonet?

74
00:02:51,963 --> 00:02:53,673
So, you're her older brother.

75
00:02:54,299 --> 00:02:56,050
Why do you want to take her back, huh?

76
00:02:56,134 --> 00:02:57,176
Aren't you angry at her?

77
00:02:57,260 --> 00:02:58,845
I'm not angry.

78
00:02:58,928 --> 00:03:00,305
I'm just hurt. That's different.

79
00:03:00,388 --> 00:03:02,265
[music continues]

80
00:03:02,348 --> 00:03:04,601
Son of a thread.

81
00:03:05,184 --> 00:03:07,103
I said stay in the car.

82
00:03:07,186 --> 00:03:10,440
[rousing music playing]

83
00:03:11,858 --> 00:03:14,402
[sauve theme music playing]

84
00:03:16,738 --> 00:03:18,573
[motorcycle revving]

85
00:03:18,656 --> 00:03:21,451
- [sewing machine whirring]
- [scratches]

86
00:03:21,534 --> 00:03:22,493
[snipping]

87
00:03:22,577 --> 00:03:24,954
[sewing machine whirring]

88
00:03:25,038 --> 00:03:26,372
[gun cocks]

89
00:03:26,456 --> 00:03:29,751
- [gunshots]
- [gunfire blasting]

90
00:03:29,834 --> 00:03:32,045
[clicking]

91
00:03:32,128 --> 00:03:34,130
[snipping]

92
00:03:34,213 --> 00:03:37,091
[electronic blipping]

93
00:03:41,387 --> 00:03:42,555
[Enzo, in English] Too late.

94
00:03:43,431 --> 00:03:45,058
She doesn't need you anymore.

95
00:03:46,059 --> 00:03:48,478
[in English] She needs someone like me.

96
00:03:48,561 --> 00:03:52,482
Not someone like you,
who always finds fault with her.

97
00:03:52,565 --> 00:03:56,152
[suspicious music playing]

98
00:03:56,236 --> 00:03:58,029
She needs a brother…

99
00:03:58,905 --> 00:04:00,281
not a kidnapper.

100
00:04:00,365 --> 00:04:02,867
- [grunting, groaning]
- [thudding]

101
00:04:02,951 --> 00:04:03,993
Netchai!

102
00:04:04,577 --> 00:04:06,955
[grunts]

103
00:04:07,038 --> 00:04:10,625
- [tense music playing]
- [growls]

104
00:04:18,049 --> 00:04:22,303
- [thuds, then clatters]
- [shouts, grunts]

105
00:04:34,857 --> 00:04:36,693
[shouts]

106
00:04:36,776 --> 00:04:39,988
[music fades]

107
00:04:40,071 --> 00:04:42,824
[groans]

108
00:04:42,907 --> 00:04:47,328
[rousing music playing]

109
00:04:48,913 --> 00:04:52,292
[crickets chirping]

110
00:04:52,375 --> 00:04:58,923
[sinister music playing]

111
00:05:19,193 --> 00:05:23,531
[dramatic buzz]

112
00:05:36,586 --> 00:05:38,087
‪[music intensifies]

113
00:05:44,594 --> 00:05:47,346
[music fades]

114
00:05:49,140 --> 00:05:50,391
Netchai!

115
00:05:54,687 --> 00:05:55,730
Netchai!

116
00:05:55,813 --> 00:05:58,983
[ominous music playing]

117
00:05:59,067 --> 00:05:59,901
‪[heavy breathing]

118
00:06:01,069 --> 00:06:01,903
‪[gasps]

119
00:06:22,006 --> 00:06:28,137
[tense music playing]

120
00:06:28,221 --> 00:06:29,514
This belongs to Netchai.

121
00:06:29,597 --> 00:06:31,516
[music intensifies]

122
00:06:35,269 --> 00:06:38,231
[music fades]

123
00:06:38,314 --> 00:06:42,693
[suspenseful music playing]

124
00:06:47,365 --> 00:06:48,658
[lock rattles]

125
00:06:54,580 --> 00:06:55,540
[zipping]

126
00:06:56,374 --> 00:07:01,671
[cool upbeat music playing]

127
00:07:06,217 --> 00:07:07,552
[door lock clicks]

128
00:07:13,141 --> 00:07:15,893
[music fades]

129
00:07:17,895 --> 00:07:18,896
[gun cocks]

130
00:07:21,524 --> 00:07:23,734
Where did you take my sister?!

131
00:07:24,277 --> 00:07:27,530
I'll take you where she isn't!

132
00:07:29,073 --> 00:07:30,283
Do you know where that is?

133
00:07:31,033 --> 00:07:32,743
To your grave!

134
00:07:32,827 --> 00:07:33,995
[growls, groans]

135
00:07:35,413 --> 00:07:36,456
There!

136
00:07:37,748 --> 00:07:41,752
[tense music playing]

137
00:07:42,712 --> 00:07:47,717
[suspenseful music playing]

138
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:18,206
Smells like vinegar.

139
00:08:19,665 --> 00:08:20,500
[object clatters]

140
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:22,585
[suspenseful music playing]

141
00:08:22,668 --> 00:08:24,629
- Tonet.
- [thudding]

142
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:26,464
Tonet?

143
00:08:31,219 --> 00:08:32,303
Tonet, Tonet.

144
00:08:34,138 --> 00:08:35,348
Shh, Tonet.

145
00:08:35,431 --> 00:08:39,018
[tense music playing]

146
00:08:43,481 --> 00:08:47,151
On a farm this big, if I dump you…

147
00:08:47,235 --> 00:08:49,862
[smirks] …no one will know.

148
00:08:49,946 --> 00:08:51,197
[cackles]

149
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:53,866
Oh, what did you think?

150
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:55,243
I have someone with me.

151
00:08:55,326 --> 00:08:57,370
He's tough, ex-military.

152
00:08:57,453 --> 00:09:02,208
- [clatters, then thuds]
- [woman mutters, whimpers]

153
00:09:02,291 --> 00:09:06,879
- [thuds]
- [mutters, gasps]

154
00:09:06,963 --> 00:09:10,466
[ominous music playing]

155
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:11,467
[woman moans]

156
00:09:11,551 --> 00:09:16,138
- [Atoy mumbles]
- [women whimpers]

157
00:09:16,806 --> 00:09:18,474
- Atoy.
- Shh. Keep quiet.

158
00:09:18,558 --> 00:09:21,185
I'll take care of you. Just stay quiet.

159
00:09:21,269 --> 00:09:22,895
Where?

160
00:09:22,979 --> 00:09:24,522
Looks like they left you, huh?

161
00:09:24,605 --> 00:09:27,316
Where? Uh…

162
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:28,776
- There. Maybe over there!
- Where?

163
00:09:28,859 --> 00:09:31,487
You just can't see him! Atoy?

164
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:32,405
‪[soft whiimpering]

165
00:09:37,410 --> 00:09:38,661
- [women whimpering]
- [Atoy] Okay.

166
00:09:38,744 --> 00:09:39,829
Shh.

167
00:09:40,413 --> 00:09:43,666
Atoy, I thought we were going to die here.

168
00:09:43,749 --> 00:09:45,543
- Thank God you're here.
- Thank you.

169
00:09:45,626 --> 00:09:47,169
- Thank you, Big Brother.
- I'll take care of you.

170
00:09:47,253 --> 00:09:49,589
Stay quiet, okay? Stay here.

171
00:09:49,672 --> 00:09:50,631
I'll go inside.

172
00:09:50,715 --> 00:09:52,633
- Enzo is with Emerson.
- [Tonet] Huh?

173
00:09:53,634 --> 00:09:55,177
Big Brother is there?

174
00:09:55,845 --> 00:09:58,306
Emerson shouldn't be with that man.

175
00:09:58,389 --> 00:09:59,307
I left him outside.

176
00:09:59,390 --> 00:10:01,350
But why-- Why are they together now?

177
00:10:01,434 --> 00:10:02,727
Atoy?

178
00:10:02,810 --> 00:10:04,520
- [grunts, gasps]
- [gunshot]

179
00:10:04,604 --> 00:10:06,147
- [squeals]
- [gasps]

180
00:10:06,230 --> 00:10:08,357
[Tonet] That's Big Brother!
Atoy, that's Big Brother!

181
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:09,358
[Atoy] Tonet, Tonet!

182
00:10:09,442 --> 00:10:10,860
[women gasping]

183
00:10:10,943 --> 00:10:11,986
Stay there, okay?

184
00:10:12,069 --> 00:10:14,864
Stay here. Don't move. Don't move.

185
00:10:14,947 --> 00:10:17,491
Just wait. I'll be back.
I'll be back. Stay there.

186
00:10:18,451 --> 00:10:20,745
[Queenie] Tonet, it's dangerous there!

187
00:10:20,828 --> 00:10:25,458
- [grunting]
- [grunting, groaning]

188
00:10:25,541 --> 00:10:28,002
- [grunts]
- [grunts]

189
00:10:30,755 --> 00:10:31,756
[gun cocks]

190
00:10:31,839 --> 00:10:33,215
- [Emerson panting]
- [music intensifies]

191
00:10:33,299 --> 00:10:35,176
- Atoy!
- [Enzo] Shut up!

192
00:10:35,259 --> 00:10:37,678
[music intensifies]

193
00:10:37,762 --> 00:10:39,847
[Emerson] No, no, no. No, no, no, no!

194
00:10:39,930 --> 00:10:41,599
- [grunts, groans]
- [thuds]

195
00:10:41,682 --> 00:10:45,061
- [tense music playing]
- [grunting]

196
00:10:45,144 --> 00:10:47,730
‪[gasping] Big Brother!

197
00:10:49,065 --> 00:10:49,899
[Emerson] Netchai!

198
00:10:49,982 --> 00:10:53,611
[music intensifies]

199
00:10:53,694 --> 00:10:55,071
[grunts, groans]

200
00:10:56,405 --> 00:10:58,240
- [thumps]
- [groans]

201
00:10:58,866 --> 00:10:59,992
[gunshot blasts]

202
00:11:00,076 --> 00:11:02,411
- [squeals]
- [thuds]

203
00:11:02,495 --> 00:11:03,412
Big Brother!

204
00:11:03,496 --> 00:11:04,872
[gasps]

205
00:11:04,955 --> 00:11:07,750
[music intensifies]

206
00:11:11,170 --> 00:11:12,546
[tense music playing]

207
00:11:12,630 --> 00:11:14,006
- [thuds]
- [groans]

208
00:11:14,590 --> 00:11:15,633
[grunts, groans]

209
00:11:18,969 --> 00:11:20,429
[Tonet] Big Brother, Big Brother.

210
00:11:20,513 --> 00:11:23,891
[sobbing]

211
00:11:24,475 --> 00:11:27,561
Big Bro… Atoy!

212
00:11:27,645 --> 00:11:30,564
Atoy! Atoy, Atoy!

213
00:11:30,648 --> 00:11:32,942
- [music fades]
- [sobbing]

214
00:11:33,025 --> 00:11:35,778
Atoy, Atoy! There's blood!

215
00:11:35,861 --> 00:11:37,321
There's blood.

216
00:11:37,405 --> 00:11:40,199
- He was shot in the head, Atoy!
- Wait, wait. Hold on.

217
00:11:40,282 --> 00:11:41,826
Let's take him to the hospital!

218
00:11:41,909 --> 00:11:43,411
Atoy. Atoy!

219
00:11:43,494 --> 00:11:47,957
[sobbing]

220
00:11:50,751 --> 00:11:53,003
[tense sting]

221
00:11:54,922 --> 00:11:56,298
[sobbing] Big Brother. Bro--

222
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:06,475
- Tonet. Tonet, Tonet. Tonet.
- [heavy breathing]

223
00:12:06,559 --> 00:12:09,937
That's not blood. It's motor oil.

224
00:12:10,020 --> 00:12:11,355
- [suspenseful music playing]
- [Tonet gasps]

225
00:12:11,439 --> 00:12:13,441
Looks like his head slammed here.

226
00:12:13,524 --> 00:12:15,818
He slipped there…

227
00:12:17,153 --> 00:12:19,196
and the bullet hit the tree.

228
00:12:23,701 --> 00:12:24,535
Big Brother?

229
00:12:24,618 --> 00:12:25,661
[heavy breathing]

230
00:12:25,744 --> 00:12:27,288
Really?

231
00:12:28,205 --> 00:12:29,123
‘Son.

232
00:12:29,665 --> 00:12:31,792
Big Brother, wake up, Big Brother!

233
00:12:33,294 --> 00:12:35,421
- So, he's not dead?
- No.

234
00:12:35,921 --> 00:12:36,755
‪[heavy breathing]

235
00:12:37,715 --> 00:12:38,799
[in English] Motor oil.

236
00:12:40,384 --> 00:12:41,677
[in English] Motor oil?

237
00:12:42,887 --> 00:12:45,890
You scared me. You're alive after all!

238
00:12:46,807 --> 00:12:47,641
Big Brother!

239
00:12:47,725 --> 00:12:50,311
[music fades]

240
00:12:53,731 --> 00:12:58,527
[crickets chirping]

241
00:13:02,573 --> 00:13:03,782
DOES MASTER CUTTER HAVE A SCHEDULE
TO COME AND MEET ME?

242
00:13:07,328 --> 00:13:10,080
[crickets chirping]

243
00:13:12,917 --> 00:13:14,793
Looks like, um…

244
00:13:14,877 --> 00:13:16,128
your text mate fell asleep.

245
00:13:17,296 --> 00:13:19,298
Although, I think that

246
00:13:19,381 --> 00:13:21,050
your text mate who sleeps early is better

247
00:13:21,133 --> 00:13:24,136
than an island fling
who forgot about you, but…

248
00:13:25,721 --> 00:13:27,181
[in English] You can do better.

249
00:13:28,557 --> 00:13:32,353
[in English] And you think you did better
by marrying my brother? Please.

250
00:13:33,062 --> 00:13:34,563
[in English] At least I know his name.

251
00:13:35,898 --> 00:13:39,026
Don't worry. I'll find him soon.

252
00:13:41,237 --> 00:13:42,446
Thank you, sis.

253
00:13:43,572 --> 00:13:45,324
[sinister music playing]

254
00:13:45,407 --> 00:13:47,910
- Ma'am, are you okay?
- [sharp exhale]

255
00:13:49,828 --> 00:13:53,832
It's just my side that hurts. [inhales]

256
00:13:53,916 --> 00:13:56,085
But my stomach doesn't hurt.

257
00:13:56,168 --> 00:13:58,295
Could it be appendicitis?

258
00:13:58,379 --> 00:13:59,672
[scoffs]

259
00:13:59,755 --> 00:14:01,340
[in English] That's impossible.

260
00:14:01,423 --> 00:14:04,009
I already had surgery for that
when I was in a coma.

261
00:14:04,093 --> 00:14:06,095
I don't have an appendix anymore.

262
00:14:06,178 --> 00:14:09,765
Ahh. But ma'am, why don't you have a scar?

263
00:14:10,474 --> 00:14:13,811
Isn't the wound supposed to be here?

264
00:14:14,603 --> 00:14:15,437
[Martina] Tess!

265
00:14:15,521 --> 00:14:16,730
- [Audrey grunts]
- So, you're a doctor, huh?

266
00:14:17,314 --> 00:14:19,441
You know, just go back to the kitchen

267
00:14:19,525 --> 00:14:22,111
and do what you need to do.

268
00:14:22,695 --> 00:14:25,197
Sorry. Apologies, ma'am.

269
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:27,783
[music swells]

270
00:14:30,244 --> 00:14:33,747
[police siren wails]

271
00:14:33,831 --> 00:14:36,000
We spoke to the registered owner
of this farm,

272
00:14:36,584 --> 00:14:39,545
Mrs. Bernadette Mallari.

273
00:14:39,628 --> 00:14:42,214
She's the aunt of the suspect,
Enzo Mallari.

274
00:14:42,882 --> 00:14:46,135
Enzo is an orphan,
raised here by his aunt.

275
00:14:47,052 --> 00:14:49,722
Two years ago, Mrs. Mallari
migrated to the US,

276
00:14:50,472 --> 00:14:53,684
leaving Enzo alone
as caretaker of the farm.

277
00:14:54,643 --> 00:14:56,228
What about Mandy Navarro?

278
00:14:56,312 --> 00:14:58,480
The missing woman. Any news?

279
00:14:58,564 --> 00:15:00,399
[crickets chirping]

280
00:15:00,482 --> 00:15:02,318
Enzo already revealed
where he buried the body.

281
00:15:02,401 --> 00:15:04,528
Our team is already confirming it.

282
00:15:04,612 --> 00:15:07,990
[dramatic sting]

283
00:15:08,073 --> 00:15:08,908
[Peping] Queenie!

284
00:15:08,991 --> 00:15:10,242
- Big Sister!
- [Peping] Queenie!

285
00:15:10,326 --> 00:15:12,786
Uncle, Sis! [wails]

286
00:15:12,870 --> 00:15:14,121
- Oh, my niece.
- [Queenie] Uncle!

287
00:15:14,204 --> 00:15:15,164
- Queenie!
- [cries]

288
00:15:15,247 --> 00:15:17,291
What were you thinking, child?

289
00:15:17,374 --> 00:15:19,793
- Tonet, Atoy.
- [crying]

290
00:15:19,877 --> 00:15:22,338
Thank you so much for saving my niece.

291
00:15:22,421 --> 00:15:25,049
[Queenie] I was so scared, sis.

292
00:15:25,132 --> 00:15:28,010
- I thought I was going to die.
- [Rachel sniffles]

293
00:15:28,093 --> 00:15:29,178
[girls crying softly]

294
00:15:29,261 --> 00:15:32,806
[Queenie] You better stop
using social media already.

295
00:15:33,432 --> 00:15:34,600
- You have no shame!
- [indistinct]

296
00:15:34,683 --> 00:15:36,685
- You're so evil!
- [indistinct]

297
00:15:36,769 --> 00:15:37,686
- [Peping] Enough!
- [Queenie] Shameless!

298
00:15:37,770 --> 00:15:40,272
- [Peping] Enough. Enough.
- [Queenie] You're so cruel!

299
00:15:41,190 --> 00:15:42,316
[in English] I'm sorry.

300
00:15:43,192 --> 00:15:45,569
I just wanted to be with you longer.

301
00:15:46,236 --> 00:15:47,947
I don't have family here anymore.
I'm alone.

302
00:15:48,030 --> 00:15:51,492
If you're lonely, you don't need
to kidnap anyone to be happy!

303
00:15:51,575 --> 00:15:53,577
Family isn't forced!

304
00:15:54,536 --> 00:15:58,165
You don't lock them up, and you don't
replace them when you get tired!

305
00:15:58,248 --> 00:16:01,085
[pensive music playing]

306
00:16:02,586 --> 00:16:04,004
Rot in jail!

307
00:16:04,088 --> 00:16:06,507
[phone ringing]

308
00:16:06,590 --> 00:16:07,591
[Peping] Enough.

309
00:16:08,342 --> 00:16:09,385
[phone clicks]

310
00:16:10,511 --> 00:16:11,345
Hello, sir.

311
00:16:11,929 --> 00:16:12,763
[Mercado] <i>Atoy.</i>

312
00:16:12,846 --> 00:16:15,933
Sorry if I'm calling you this late.

313
00:16:16,016 --> 00:16:19,770
Audrey Regalia has sent me
several messages.

314
00:16:19,853 --> 00:16:23,107
She's asking about your meet-up schedule.

315
00:16:23,190 --> 00:16:24,274
[scoffs]

316
00:16:24,858 --> 00:16:26,443
She can't wait, huh.

317
00:16:30,364 --> 00:16:31,865
I'm just finishing some work, sir.

318
00:16:32,700 --> 00:16:33,617
[in English] How was it?

319
00:16:34,201 --> 00:16:35,744
[in English] Subject secured.

320
00:16:36,537 --> 00:16:37,788
[in English] Situation stable.

321
00:16:37,871 --> 00:16:41,000
["Tailor" playing]

322
00:16:42,543 --> 00:16:44,795
Let's just say…

323
00:16:44,878 --> 00:16:47,131
there's no tear that cannot be sewn.

324
00:16:57,808 --> 00:17:02,062
[crickets chirping]

325
00:17:02,146 --> 00:17:05,315
[pensive music playing]

326
00:17:06,316 --> 00:17:08,944
Ma'am? Do you need anything?

327
00:17:10,237 --> 00:17:11,280
[inhales]

328
00:17:11,363 --> 00:17:13,991
You know, Tess, you're fine,

329
00:17:14,074 --> 00:17:16,869
but you're too close to Audrey.

330
00:17:16,952 --> 00:17:18,495
No, ma'am.

331
00:17:18,579 --> 00:17:20,414
I was just curious.

332
00:17:21,415 --> 00:17:25,836
She said she had her appendix removed.

333
00:17:25,919 --> 00:17:30,299
But she doesn't have a scar
on her right side.

334
00:17:30,966 --> 00:17:34,178
I had appendicitis before, so I know.

335
00:17:35,012 --> 00:17:38,098
You know, maybe you
should pack your things.

336
00:17:38,182 --> 00:17:39,183
Leave.

337
00:17:39,266 --> 00:17:40,309
What?

338
00:17:40,392 --> 00:17:41,894
- Ma'am, I didn't do anything wrong.
- [Martina] You don't want to?

339
00:17:42,519 --> 00:17:43,604
- Ma'am, please have mercy--
- I said leave.

340
00:17:43,687 --> 00:17:44,938
- Ma'am… Ma'am!
- Hurry up!

341
00:17:45,022 --> 00:17:46,106
- Leave! Pack up!
- Ma'am!

342
00:17:46,190 --> 00:17:47,900
Hurry, hurry! Quick, quick, quick!

343
00:17:47,983 --> 00:17:49,443
- You're prioritizing gossip…
- I didn't do anything wrong, ma'am.

344
00:17:49,526 --> 00:17:52,529
- Hurry up, hurry up!
- Ma'am, please, have mercy!

345
00:17:52,613 --> 00:17:55,616
You're so slow! So slow!

346
00:17:56,450 --> 00:17:57,534
Get out!

347
00:17:57,618 --> 00:17:58,869
[tense music playing]

348
00:17:58,952 --> 00:18:00,496
Sorry, ma'am.

349
00:18:03,624 --> 00:18:04,708
[sighs]

350
00:18:04,792 --> 00:18:09,088
[music fades]

351
00:18:09,171 --> 00:18:13,634
[machine whirring]

352
00:18:24,144 --> 00:18:27,648
- [pensive music playing]
- [phone ringing]

353
00:18:28,649 --> 00:18:31,068
Uh-- -Um, Mr. Mercado!

354
00:18:31,151 --> 00:18:32,778
[in English] G-good morning.

355
00:18:32,861 --> 00:18:35,239
My tracker is available today.

356
00:18:35,322 --> 00:18:36,657
Eastridge Hospital.

357
00:18:37,324 --> 00:18:38,408
[Mercado, in English] <i>Ground floor.</i>

358
00:18:38,492 --> 00:18:42,162
<i>Garden area, 10:30 a.m. Don't be late.</i>

359
00:18:42,246 --> 00:18:44,581
How will I know who he is?

360
00:18:44,665 --> 00:18:46,542
What's his name?

361
00:18:46,625 --> 00:18:48,127
He'll be carrying coffee.

362
00:18:48,210 --> 00:18:50,587
Just call him The Master Cutter.

363
00:18:50,671 --> 00:18:52,005
- [in English] Copy?
- [in English] Okay!

364
00:18:52,089 --> 00:18:56,009
[in English] 10:30 a.m., Eastridge,
The Master Cutter. Got it.

365
00:18:56,635 --> 00:18:59,096
Uh, how about…

366
00:18:59,179 --> 00:19:00,264
[line beeping]

367
00:19:00,347 --> 00:19:02,724
H-hello? Hello?

368
00:19:02,808 --> 00:19:04,726
[line beeping]

369
00:19:05,352 --> 00:19:06,353
Who were you talking to?

370
00:19:06,854 --> 00:19:09,064
[tense music playing]

371
00:19:09,148 --> 00:19:10,232
No one.

372
00:19:22,494 --> 00:19:24,121
[indistinct chattering]

373
00:19:24,204 --> 00:19:25,330
[man] Is that okay?

374
00:19:26,165 --> 00:19:27,541
Mmm.

375
00:19:27,624 --> 00:19:33,881
- [somber music playing]
- [indistinct chattering]

376
00:19:35,382 --> 00:19:36,800
Take it with you.

377
00:19:39,511 --> 00:19:41,096
- Just take it.
- Wake up.

378
00:19:42,514 --> 00:19:43,932
[T-bak] Brother Emerson?

379
00:19:44,016 --> 00:19:45,100
[in English] How are you feeling?

380
00:19:45,184 --> 00:19:46,435
Hey. Are you sick?

381
00:19:46,518 --> 00:19:47,769
Don't bother Emerson.

382
00:19:52,774 --> 00:19:53,859
I'm fine.

383
00:19:54,526 --> 00:19:57,196
Brother Emerson, why is it
that you look like a victim?

384
00:19:57,279 --> 00:19:58,864
Were you kidnapped too?

385
00:19:58,947 --> 00:20:01,491
- Psst, hey. What's the matter with you?
- Sorry, brother.

386
00:20:01,575 --> 00:20:03,702
Brother Emerson, just testing.

387
00:20:03,785 --> 00:20:05,454
How many fingers?

388
00:20:07,122 --> 00:20:08,123
Three.

389
00:20:08,207 --> 00:20:09,875
- Me, me. Me, me.
- [overlapping chatter]

390
00:20:09,958 --> 00:20:11,376
Do you recognize me?

391
00:20:13,295 --> 00:20:14,880
You're crazy, Tukmol.

392
00:20:14,963 --> 00:20:16,381
You owe me a lot.

393
00:20:16,465 --> 00:20:18,550
- [laughing]
- [lively chattering]

394
00:20:18,634 --> 00:20:19,676
Still remembers the debt.

395
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:20,719
- [overlapping chatter]
- How much?

396
00:20:20,802 --> 00:20:21,887
No loose screws here.

397
00:20:21,970 --> 00:20:23,430
[Bebang, in Engish] Thank you, Lord!

398
00:20:23,513 --> 00:20:26,308
God is good, right? Oh!

399
00:20:27,017 --> 00:20:28,894
Emerson, did you know,

400
00:20:28,977 --> 00:20:33,857
Atoy said you saved Father Peping's niece

401
00:20:33,941 --> 00:20:34,775
and Tonet too.

402
00:20:34,858 --> 00:20:37,319
- [man] Yes. Ahh! Amazing!
- [Karla] You're the man, Brother Emerson!

403
00:20:37,402 --> 00:20:39,404
- [T-bak] Whoo!
- [in English] It's giving!

404
00:20:39,488 --> 00:20:40,572
Oh, right?

405
00:20:40,656 --> 00:20:44,243
The new hero of Barangay Tabang Lupa!

406
00:20:44,326 --> 00:20:45,285
- [cheering]
- Correct!

407
00:20:45,369 --> 00:20:50,374
- [cheering]
- Emerson! Emerson! Emerson!

408
00:20:50,457 --> 00:20:54,336
- Emerson! Emerson! Emerson!
- [Emerson] Wait, wait, wait, wait.

409
00:20:54,419 --> 00:20:55,379
Wait a minute. Where's…

410
00:20:55,462 --> 00:20:57,047
Where's my sister?

411
00:20:57,130 --> 00:20:58,590
Where's Netchai?

412
00:20:58,674 --> 00:21:01,301
Big Brother! Big Brother!

413
00:21:01,385 --> 00:21:03,553
[speaking in Visayan]
I'm right here, Big Brother.

414
00:21:03,637 --> 00:21:08,016
I never left your side.

415
00:21:08,809 --> 00:21:11,061
Hmm. How are you?

416
00:21:11,144 --> 00:21:12,729
Were you hurt?

417
00:21:12,813 --> 00:21:14,982
What did that man do to you?

418
00:21:15,065 --> 00:21:17,442
- I'll go back for that monster--
- No, no more.

419
00:21:17,526 --> 00:21:18,944
No more. Don't.

420
00:21:19,027 --> 00:21:20,821
Nothing. Nothing, see? Nothing. I'm okay.

421
00:21:20,904 --> 00:21:23,323
[speaking in Visayan]
What matters is that you're safe too.

422
00:21:23,407 --> 00:21:25,534
Nothing bad happened to you.

423
00:21:26,660 --> 00:21:28,870
[Bebang] Wow! I'm touched!

424
00:21:28,954 --> 00:21:30,580
[chuckles] But wait.

425
00:21:30,664 --> 00:21:32,249
They're reconciled now, right?

426
00:21:32,332 --> 00:21:33,250
Looks like it?

427
00:21:33,333 --> 00:21:35,460
- Wish there were subtitles.
- Yes, right.

428
00:21:35,544 --> 00:21:37,045
- You guys!
- [laughs]

429
00:21:37,129 --> 00:21:39,756
No subtitles needed for sibling love.

430
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:40,966
[Karla] Yay!

431
00:21:41,049 --> 00:21:43,677
- [Karla] Finally, you said something nice.
- Mmm-mmm.

432
00:21:44,386 --> 00:21:45,929
- Just kidding.
- [laughs]

433
00:21:46,013 --> 00:21:48,682
- [overlapping chatter]
- Stop joking around.

434
00:21:48,765 --> 00:21:50,267
[tense sting]

435
00:21:50,350 --> 00:21:53,937
Ah, I just need to meet someone.

436
00:21:54,563 --> 00:21:55,397
You guys handle things here.

437
00:21:55,480 --> 00:21:57,107
All right, Brother.

438
00:21:57,190 --> 00:21:59,901
- [sentimental music playing]
- [indistinct chattering]

439
00:22:04,823 --> 00:22:06,867
Dad, coffee.

440
00:22:07,701 --> 00:22:09,494
Is Audrey awake?

441
00:22:09,578 --> 00:22:10,537
[Red groans]

442
00:22:10,620 --> 00:22:12,956
I-- I saw her in the kitchen earlier.

443
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:16,335
Tell her to come with me to the cemetery.

444
00:22:16,418 --> 00:22:18,628
It's my wedding anniversary with your mom.

445
00:22:19,421 --> 00:22:21,340
Oh, I'll go instead.
She seems to have plans.

446
00:22:21,423 --> 00:22:22,257
[Dmitri scoffs]

447
00:22:22,341 --> 00:22:24,176
You?

448
00:22:24,259 --> 00:22:25,844
[in English] I'd rather go alone.

449
00:22:25,927 --> 00:22:27,012
[sinister music playing]

450
00:22:27,095 --> 00:22:28,930
Do you know where she's going?

451
00:22:29,556 --> 00:22:32,100
I think to have clothes made by a tailor.

452
00:22:32,768 --> 00:22:35,353
By… the Master Cutter, I think.

453
00:22:35,437 --> 00:22:37,022
That's what I heard.

454
00:22:37,939 --> 00:22:40,025
[in English] No. No way.

455
00:22:40,108 --> 00:22:41,985
The Master Cutter isn't a tailor.

456
00:22:43,612 --> 00:22:49,618
[tense music playing]

457
00:22:55,874 --> 00:23:01,088
[epic music playing]

458
00:23:01,171 --> 00:23:03,340
[electronic blipping]

459
00:23:03,423 --> 00:23:06,927
[energetic rock music playing]

460
00:23:11,389 --> 00:23:14,017
So, this Master Cutter is a tracker?

461
00:23:14,101 --> 00:23:14,935
Not a tailor?

462
00:23:15,018 --> 00:23:18,313
[in English] And now, Audrey wants
to hire him to look for this guy.

463
00:23:18,396 --> 00:23:20,524
- [in English] Miss, Miss! Your shades.
- [indistinct]

464
00:23:20,607 --> 00:23:21,942
Do you want me to give them to her?

465
00:23:22,025 --> 00:23:23,443
[in English] Tell your tracker
to back off.

466
00:23:23,527 --> 00:23:25,987
[Dmitri] <i>And don't meet with my daughter.</i>

467
00:23:26,071 --> 00:23:27,155
UP NEXT

468
00:23:27,239 --> 00:23:30,033
My shades. Where are they?

469
00:23:30,117 --> 00:23:32,285
[Mercado, in English] <i>Abort engagement</i>
<i>with Audrey Regalia.</i>

470
00:23:32,369 --> 00:23:36,373
Mr. Regalia requested
not to meet with his daughter.

471
00:23:36,456 --> 00:23:38,041
[in English] Copy that, sir.

472
00:23:38,125 --> 00:23:40,377
[Atoy] <i>I haven't established contact</i>
<i>with the subject yet.</i>

473
00:23:40,961 --> 00:23:44,464
Miss? Miss in yellow… Is this yours?

474
00:23:44,548 --> 00:23:45,924
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

475
00:23:46,007 --> 00:23:48,176
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

476
00:23:48,260 --> 00:23:51,263
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪
